			<div class="text" id="comment-73016042477">

				<strong class="title">General Comment</strong>The song was written during the Cuban Missile Crisis, when the people that were thinking about all the possible results of the Kennedy-Khruschev confrontation were terrified of the approaching oblivion. Dylan had said that every line in the song is the start of a whole song, he decided to put all of them together as one song because he thought he wouldnt have enough time alive to write all those individual songs. It came out beautifully, and theres actually one cover of it that i think is excellent by Jason Mraz, he interprets it so well.				
