				<strong class="title">Song Meaning</strong>I always thought that the "blue eyed son" was the first A-bomb dropped on Horoshima. It was called 'little boy', hence blue eyed son was the son of America. The hard rain is the radioactive fallout. Survivors talked about 'black rain' falling out of the sky after the bomb went off. This was infact globules of dust thrown up by the explosion and formed 'droplets' as the dust was ionised by the radiation and fell to earth as black 'hard rain'.				
